(1, 'isolate', 'isolate', '隔离，孤立 (v.)', 'v.', '/''aɪsəleɪt/', '{"meaning":"隔离，孤立 (v.)","examples":["The town was isolated by the floods. — 洪水使该镇与外界隔绝。","The US has sought to isolate Cuba both economically and politically. — 美国一直想在经济和政治上孤立古巴。","protein isolate — 分离蛋白"],"etymology":null}', 2986),
(1, 'issue', 'issue', '出版，问题，发行 (n.)；分发，出版，发行 (v.)', 'n.', '/''ɪʃuː; ''ɪsjuː/', '{"meaning":"出版，问题，发行 (n.)；分发，出版，发行 (v.)","examples":["Abortion is a highly controversial issue. — 堕胎是个很有争议的话题。","We should raise the issue of discrimination with the council. — 我们应提请市政会讨论歧视的问题。","The key issue is whether workers should be classified as ‘employees’. — 关键问题是工人是否应该界定为“雇员”。"],"etymology":null}', 2987),
(1, 'item', 'item', '条款，项目，一条(新闻) (n.)', 'n.', '/''aɪtəm/', '{"meaning":"条款，项目，一条(新闻) (n.)","examples":["He opened the cardboard box and took out each item. — 他打开纸板箱把里面的物品一一拿出来。","The store is having a sale on furniture and household items. — 这家商店正在减价出售家具和家居用品。","luxury items such as exotic spices and perfumes — 异国香料和香水之类的奢侈品"],"etymology":null}', 2988),
