(1, 'leap', 'leap', '扑向，欣然接受 (v.)；跳，跃 (n.)', 'v.', '/liːp/', '{"meaning":"扑向，欣然接受 (v.)；跳，跃 (n.)","examples":["He threw a stick into the river and the dog went after it in a flying leap. — 他把一根枝条扔到河里，那条狗一个飞跃就追了过去。","by leaps and bounds — adv. 飞跃地，突飞猛进地","leap forward — 跃进；向前跳；快速发展"],"etymology":null}', 2999),
