(1, 'ludicrous', 'ludicrous', '荒谬的，可笑的 (adj.)', 'adj.', '/''luːdɪkrəs; ''ljuː-/', '{"meaning":"荒谬的，可笑的 (adj.)","examples":["It is ludicrous to suggest that I was driving under the influence of alcohol. — 说我酒后驾车，这真是太荒唐了。","The court granted him the ludicrous sum of £100 in damages. — 法院裁定他获得区区100英镑损害赔偿。","That’s a ludicrous idea. — 这个想法很荒唐。"],"etymology":null}', 3013),
