(1, 'microprocessor', 'microprocessor', '微处理器 (n.)', 'n.', '/ˌmaɪkrəu''prəusesə(r)/', '{"meaning":"微处理器 (n.)","examples":["The invention of the microprocessor had made it possible for ordinary people like you and me to actually own a computer. — 微处理器的发明，使普通老百姓（就如你和我）真正拥有一台计算机成为可能。","Early microprocessor speed and functionality while still not high enough, but can be adopted to solve the multi-processor architecture. — 早期的微处理器速度和功能虽还不够高，但可以通过多处理器结构来解决。","During the early years of microprocessors, there were few engineers witheducation and experience in the applications of microprocessor technology. — 在最初几年的微处理器，有几个工程师的教育和经验，在应用的微处理器技术。"],"etymology":null}', 4970),
